  "prompt": "What should you do if you're scratched by a stray cat that draws blood?",
  "response": "If you're scratched by a stray cat that draws blood, you should:\n\n1. Immediately wash the wound thoroughly with soap and running water for at least 5-10 minutes\n\n2. Apply an antiseptic like hydrogen peroxide or rubbing alcohol\n\n3. Apply an antibiotic ointment and cover with a clean bandage\n\n4. Seek medical attention, especially if:\n- The wound is deep\n- The cat appears sick or aggressive\n- You're unsure of the cat's vaccination history\n- You haven't had a tetanus shot recently\n\n5. Try to report the incident and, if possible, have the cat captured for rabies observation\n\n6. Monitor the wound for signs of infection like redness, swelling, warmth, or increased pain\n\nConsulting a healthcare professional is recommended to assess the risk of rabies or other potential infections.",
